    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Wnt7a-Dvl1 signalling regulates release probability at glutamatergic synapses in the hippocampus\"\n\nFig.3: \"Acute exposure to Wnt7a increases release probability without affecting synapse number in mature hippocampal neurons\"\n\nFig.4: \"Wnt signalling regulates synaptic vesicle number\".\n\nFig.5: \"Wnt signalling regulates the RRP size\"\n\nFig.6: \"Wnt signalling regulates SNARE complex formation and Dvl1 interacts with proteins of the release machinery\"\n\nFig.7: \"Wnts modulate the interaction between Dvl1 and Syt-1\"\n\nFig.8: \"Binding between Dvl1 and Syt-1 is required for normal neurotransmitter release\". Experimental description: - \"However, the in vivo requirement for Wnt signalling in neurotransmitter release has not been investigated. To address this issue, we examined Wnt-deficient mice lacking both Wnt7a and Dvl1 (Wnt7a; Dvl1 knock-out (KO)), as these mice exhibit a stronger phenotype than Wnt7a or Dvl1 single mutants25,28. \"",
